## Analysis Summary

### The Gap: Agent Spawn Errors Are Not Tracked in Metrics

**Problem Location**: `src/agents/core/BaseAgentAdapter.ts:362-364`

```typescript
child.on('error', (error) => {
  reject(new Error(`Failed to start ${this.displayName}: ${error.message}`));
});
```

**What happens when agent fails to spawn:**
1. ‚úÖ Error is caught and rejected
2. ‚úÖ Proxy is cleaned up (line 414-420)
3. ‚ùå **Metrics are NOT finalized** - `metricsOrchestrator.onAgentExit()` is never called
4. ‚ùå **No error status recorded** - Session status stays "active" instead of "failed"
5. ‚ùå **No lifecycle hooks executed** - `onSessionEnd` and `afterRun` are skipped

**Why this matters:**
- Spawn errors (command not found, permission denied, invalid args) are invisible to metrics
- Session status in `~/.codemie/metrics/sessions/` remains "active" indefinitely
- Analytics dashboards won't show these failures
- Users can't track which agents fail to start and why

### Comparison: Exit vs Spawn Error Handling

| Event | Metrics Tracked? | Status Updated? | Lifecycle Hooks? |
|-------|-----------------|-----------------|------------------|
| **Normal exit** (line 366) | ‚úÖ Yes | ‚úÖ Yes | ‚úÖ Yes |
| **Spawn error** (line 362) | ‚ùå No | ‚ùå No | ‚ùå No |
| **Sync try-catch** (line 414) | ‚ùå No | ‚ùå No | ‚ùå No |

### Recommendation

Add error tracking in the spawn error handler:

```typescript
child.on('error', async (error) => {
  // Finalize metrics with error status
  if (this.metricsOrchestrator) {
    await this.metricsOrchestrator.onAgentExit(1); // Exit code 1 = error
  }

  // Execute lifecycle hooks
  await executeOnSessionEnd(this, this.metadata.lifecycle, this.metadata.name, 1, env);

  // Clean up
  await cleanup();

  await executeAfterRun(this, this.metadata.lifecycle, this.metadata.name, 1, env);

  reject(new Error(`Failed to start ${this.displayName}: ${error.message}`));
});
```

This would ensure:
- ‚úÖ Spawn failures are recorded in metrics
- ‚úÖ Session status is updated to "failed"
- ‚úÖ Analytics can track startup failure rates
- ‚úÖ Lifecycle hooks execute for error cases
- ‚úÖ Consistent error handling across all failure modes

Would you like me to implement this fix?

