Perfect! I've successfully implemented global error handling for agent startup failures with metrics tracking. Here's what changed:

## Changes Made

### 1. **Spawn Error Handler** (BaseAgentAdapter.ts:362-382)
Now tracks metrics when the agent process fails to start (e.g., command not found, permission denied):

```typescript
child.on('error', async (error) => {
  // Remove signal handlers to prevent memory leaks
  process.off('SIGINT', sigintHandler);
  process.off('SIGTERM', sigtermHandler);

  // Finalize metrics with error status
  if (this.metricsOrchestrator) {
    await this.metricsOrchestrator.onAgentExit(1); // Exit code 1 = spawn error
  }

  // Lifecycle hook: session end (provider-aware)
  await executeOnSessionEnd(this, this.metadata.lifecycle, this.metadata.name, 1, env);

  // Clean up proxy
  await cleanup();

  // Lifecycle hook: afterRun (provider-aware)
  await executeAfterRun(this, this.metadata.lifecycle, this.metadata.name, 1, env);

  reject(new Error(`Failed to start ${this.displayName}: ${error.message}`));
});
```

### 2. **Synchronous Try-Catch Block** (BaseAgentAdapter.ts:432-451)
Now tracks metrics for synchronous errors during spawn setup:

```typescript
} catch (error) {
  // Finalize metrics with error status
  if (this.metricsOrchestrator) {
    await this.metricsOrchestrator.onAgentExit(1); // Exit code 1 = error
  }

  // Lifecycle hook: session end (provider-aware)
  await executeOnSessionEnd(this, this.metadata.lifecycle, this.metadata.name, 1, env);

  // Clean up proxy on error
  if (this.proxy) {
    await this.proxy.stop();
    this.proxy = null;
  }

  // Lifecycle hook: afterRun (provider-aware)
  await executeAfterRun(this, this.metadata.lifecycle, this.metadata.name, 1, env);

  throw error;
}
```

## What This Fixes

‚úÖ **Metrics now tracked for all failure modes:**
- Spawn failures (command not found, permission errors)
- Synchronous errors during setup
- Normal exit failures (already working)

‚úÖ **Session status correctly updated:**
- Sessions marked as "failed" in `~/.codemie/metrics/sessions/`
- Exit code 1 recorded for error cases

‚úÖ **Lifecycle hooks execute consistently:**
- `onSessionEnd` called for all error paths
- `afterRun` called for all error paths

‚úÖ **Analytics visibility:**
- Startup failure rates visible in dashboards
- Error tracking across all agents

## Testing

Build and lint passed successfully:
- ‚úÖ TypeScript compilation successful
- ‚úÖ ESLint passed (0 warnings)

The error handling is now consistent across all failure modes, ensuring comprehensive metrics tracking for monitoring agent health and troubleshooting issues.

